						<summary>

						<p>The inscription belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva (Vikramāditya VI)</hi> and is much damaged. It seems to register the gift of some land to a temple. It mentions Bāhubali, the disciple of [Indra]ṇandi of the Mūla-<hi rend="italic">saṅgha,</hi> Dēśīya-<hi rend="italic">gaṇa,</hi> Pustaka<hi rend="italic">gachchha</hi> and Kuṇḍakund-<hi rend="italic">ānvaya,</hi> who built the temple.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 9 • • • • Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti.</hi> The details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
